caption:
As antithetical as l am towards this year's election
 l resonate with this
 ideology heavily
 There's this underlying shameful feeling of acquiesce, knowing that my
 party is essentially irrelevant, just like any vote (or lack of) in opposition,
 and even our votes in general are just as good as a lottery ticket. The
 election is preordained and pretty much out of our control, yet the pressure
 to vote for a braggadocio or fabulist believing that it'll create a more
 favorable result from the lesser of two evils will actually not mitigate the
 power of the our erroneous system. And by doing so, you are advocating
 as an autocratic catalyst for the suppression of change, or you're at least
 succumbing to it. Either way, it's not making a (positive) difference
 What have to take away from this year's election is contentment
 and more than anything, a sense of Liberty. The real pressure should be to
 vote for who and what you have faith in, preserving what little authenticity
 there is left in the election. It is all so disgustingly dissatisfying and will be
 there's an ameliorated political change in our country, but that won't
 happen by doing the same thing over and over again expecting a different
 result.
